fsrilanka(gbcsl)6399cd91dfecf',1,'-','The Green Building Council of Sri Lanka (GBCSL) is the Sri Lanka’s leading authority on implementing green concept and green building practices.','Over 100','gm.gbcsl@gmail.com',NULL,'[]',NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,'[]',1000,1000,1,'2022-12-14 13:24:27','2022-12-14 13:24:27',NULL,'[\"2022\\/12\\/121420221324026399ce72352d1.jpeg\"]',NULL,NULL,'[]','[]'),(14,15,'Wildlife and Nature Protection Society of Sri Lanka (WNPS)','wildlifeandnatureprotectionsocietyofsrilanka(wnps)6399cdfc90fb7',1,'1968 Act 29','Wildlife and Nature Protection society is the third oldest conservation organization in the world and the first in Sri Lanka. We have 128th years of history.','11 - 30','research@wnpssl.org',NULL,'[]',NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,'[]',1000,1000,1,'2022-12-14 13:22:04','2022-12-14 13:22:04',NULL,'',NULL,NULL,'[]','[]'),(15,16,'Rainforest Protectors of Sri Lanka','rainforestprotectorsofsrilanka6399ce37e78f0',4,'# 6/6/17/01/146','Rainforest Protectors of Sri Lanka is a non-profit environmental organization with a mission to protect the last remaining rainforests and threatened ecosystems in Sri Lanka including Sinharaja and Kanneliya rainforests through conservation projects and environmental activism primarily driven through volunteer support. Rainforest Protectors also engage in investigation, reporting and finding resolutions to urgent threats faced by our rainforests and wildlife through discussions with relevant authorities and stakeholders.','Over 100','rainforestprotectors@gmail.com',NULL,'[]',NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,'[]',1000,1000,1,'2022-12-14 13:23:03','2022-12-14 13:23:03',NULL,'[]',NULL,NULL,'[]','[]'),(16,17,'The Institute for Monitoring and Evaluation','theinstituteformonitoringandevaluation6399ce46ca92c',4,'PV 102892','The Institute for Monitoring and Evaluation is a young institution, established in 2014 under the Companies Act of Sri Lanka with the exclusive purpose of bringing together experts from various disciplines to provide services for the State and Corporate sector institutions, Civil Society Organizations and the communities who are in need of ingenuous analysis, programs and evaluations on social, political, legal and economic disciplines to make a peaceful development in the country. \nTiME entered into the partnership with the Change the Game Academy in the Netherlands and have exclusive rights to conduct the training programs of the Change the Game Academy (CtGA -https://www.changethegameacademy.org/ \n   ) in Sri Lanka.  CtGA is the academic arm of the Wilde Ganzen Foundation in the Netherlands. Under this partnership, TiME is geared to build capacities of local CSOs and NGOs on the advocacy and lobby and Local Fund raising. Local Fundraising is a training module developed to find answers for the drying out of international funding to developing countries.  CtGA carries out these training programs in 15 countries in Africa, Asia, and Carribean region.\nTiME is working towards becoming a leading training institution in advocacy and lobbying and local fundraising in Sri Lanka.','1 - 10','sdaskara@gmail.com','17A, Campbell Terrace, Colombo 10, Sri Lanka','[]','http://www.institute.lk/','+94 77 2249423','Sheela Daskara','+94 777304172','Dr. Dayani Panagoda','Director','+94 772249423','Sheela Daskara','Chief Operations Officer',NULL,'sdaskara@gmail.com','https://www.linkedin.com/comm/in/sheela-daskara-00a38317?',NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,'[]',1000,1000,1,'2022-12-19 09:11:41','2022-12-19 09:11:41',NULL,'[]',NULL,NULL,'[]','[]'),(17,18,'RARE - Rally for Animal Rights & Enviornment','rarerallyforanimalrights&enviornment6399cea48a795',1,'GA00257689','We are an animal rights advocacy organisation with a vision to create a world where all sentient beings have equal rights and autonomy. Founded in 2019, we are a registered Non Profit Association in Sri Lanka. \n\nSri Lanka is a biodiversity hotspot and home to asian elephant sub species Elephas maximus maximus and the species is listed \"Endangered\" by the IUCN. But Sri Lanka reports one of the worst human elephant conflict cases and one of the cruelest captive elephant industries of the world.\n\nRARE has been recognised as the voice of the Sri Lankan elephant by elephant advocates and elephant lovers across the globe. \n\nNot just elephants we work to expose and fight against cruelty inflicted on all animals, whether they are wild, domesticated, farm or companion animals and We strive to make human beings understand that non humans have rights to mother earth just like humans and that right is not less than that of the humans.','1 - 10','panchali.raredirector@gmail.com',NULL,'[]',NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,'[]',1000,1000,1,'2022-12-14 13:30:36','2022-12-14 13:30:36',NULL,'[]',NULL,NULL,'[]','[]'),(18,19,'Rainforest Protectors Trust','rainforestprotectorstrust6399d0893f736',4,'# 6/6/17/01/146','Rainforest Protectors Trust focuses on saving real acres of rainforest in Sri Lanka through purchase and permanent conservation of privately held forest lands adjoining Sinharaja World Heritage Rainforest. Creating a Protected Buffer Zone for Sinharaja rainforest and a Biodiversity Forest Corridor to connect fragmented patches of forest to the North of Sinharaja is our top priority aimed at preventing encroachment of forest and deforestation.\n\nHaving lost more than 95% of the original rainforests during the past century, we are fighting against time to protect what is remaining in this vital ecosystem which is home to most of Sri Lanka\'s endemic and endangered flora and fauna.','Over 100','rainforestprotectorstrust@gmail.com',NULL,'[]',NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,'[]',1000,1000,1,'2022-12-14 13:32:57','2022-12-14 13:32:57',NULL,'',NULL,NULL,'[]','[]'),(19,20,'Sri Lanka Association of Inbound Tour Operators','srilankaassociationofinboundtouroperators63b7974ad8f0d',4,'12442315235','The Sri Lanka Association of Inbound Tour Operators (SLAITO) is the apex body for the inbound tourism industry in Sri Lanka. SLAITO has been the most influential institution in guiding policymakers in Sri Lanka to overcome the challenges faced by the industry. The objective of SLAITO is to represent the interests of all stakeholders and ensure that Sri Lanka takes its rightful place in the global tourism community and provides sustainable tourism growth.','Over 100','maxime.slaitoyouth@gmail.com','Ceylon Chamber of Commerce, No 50 Navam Mawatha, Colombo 2','[{\"social_media\":\"https:\\/\\/www.facebook.com\\/slaitolive\"},{\"social_media\":\"https:\\/\\/www.instagram.com\\/slaito_insta\\/\"}]','https://www.slaito.com','0771929971','Maxime Wickramasinghe',NULL,'Nishad Wijetunga','President',NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,'Sustainable Tourism Development','High Level Lobbying & Ground Level Implementation.','https://www.slaito.com','[{\"lat\":6.918484809298131,\"lng\":79.85002307414629}]',1000,1000,1,'2023-01-06 04:01:08','2023-01-06 04:01:08',NULL,'[\"2023\\/01\\/0106202304005263b79cf40d522.png\"]',NULL,NULL,'[]','[]'),(20,21,'Human Development Foundation of Sri Lanka','humandevelopmentfoundationofsrilanka63b7992e7e2b9',1,'L173002','Established in 1994 in the Badulla district, HDFSL is a well-established community based\nnon-governmental organisation which now functions as national level Social Enterprise \nwhich has initiated and successfully completed projects in districts of Hambantota,Matara and Colombo working with and under the purview of both local and \ninternational organisations such as Asian Development Bank (ADB), UNDP, Ministry of \nMahaweli Development & Environment, Environmental Authority and National Peace \nCouncil to name a few. HDFSL has an active member base of 600 who work on a voluntary \nbasis and a permanent staff base of 15 who are being paid and sustained for over a period \nof 29 years. The staffs at HDFSL are experienced, exposed and well-connected which has \nhelped the organisation to deliver the projects they undertake quit successfully and \nefficiently.\nRegistered under the NGO secretary office in all island.','Over 100','hdfofsl@gmail.com','265/1/B,watareka,padukka','[]',NULL,'0762545835',NULL,'0762545835','Sunethra','Marasinghe',NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,'[]',1000,1000,1,'2023-01-06 13:05:53','2023-01-06 13:05:53',NULL,'[]',NULL,NULL,'[]','[]'),(21,22,'test org','testorg63be369b3d94d',3,'-','dfsdfsfd','11 - 30','test1@test.com',NULL,'[]',NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,'[]',1000,1000,1,'2023-01-11 04:10:03','2023-01-11 04:10:03',NULL,'',NULL,NULL,'[]','[]'),(22,23,'Biodiversity Conservation and Research Circle','biodiversityconservationandresearchcircle63bf754a3b96e',1,'-','Organization involved in conservation activities and research related to environmental conservation and managment.','1 - 10','prakashtgsl@gmail.com',NULL,'[]',NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,'[]',1000,1000,1,'2023-01-12 02:49:46','2023-01-12 02:49:46',NULL,'',NULL,NULL,'[]','[]'),(23,26,'Organization','organization63f716c2a0909',2,'123456789','Abcd','11 - 30','organization@feo.lk',NULL,'[]',NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,'[{\"lat\":7.205063670002919,\"lng\":79.84206593852257}]',1000,1000,1,'2023-02-23 07:33:22','2023-02-23 07:34:19',NULL,'',NULL,NULL,'[]','[]'),(24,30,'testadmin','testadmin63fe99085b245',2,'testadmin','testadmin','11 - 30','testadmin@testadmin.com',NULL,'[]',NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,'[]',1000,1000,1,'2023-03-01 00:15:04',